They were building a home together, but they had not consummated that marriage yet.

21:12.345 --> 21:17.172
And so when we look at that, we shouldn't say, oh, how old-fashioned, or how quaint, or how unrealistic.

21:17.192 --> 21:21.778
We should think how honorable, how godly, how inspiring this is.

21:22.850 --> 21:29.638
In fact, it's even wilder because in a Jewish context, they would have pretty much been considered husband and wife.

21:31.059 --> 21:33.262
So Mary asked the angel, how can this be?

21:33.782 --> 21:35.664
Since I've had not had sexual relations with a man.

21:35.945 --> 21:44.154
And the angel replied to her, the Holy Spirit will come upon you and the power of the most high will overshadow you.

21:44.174 --> 21:47.698
Therefore, the Holy One to be born will be called the son of God.

21:48.386 --> 21:52.351
and consider your relative Elizabeth, even she has conceived a son in her old age.

21:52.691 --> 21:59.920
And this is the six month for her who was called Childless, for nothing will be impossible with God.

22:01.342 --> 22:07.590
Now imagine if you can't be in Mary's shoes for a second, how unbelievable is your life now?

22:08.691 --> 22:11.795
Like everything has been just completely turned upside down.

22:11.935 --> 22:17.682
How would you respond to something that was absolutely impossible without God?

22:18.434 --> 22:21.700
Here's her response, verse 38, I am the Lord's servant.

22:21.981 --> 22:25.287
May it happen to me as you have said.

22:25.327 --> 22:29.114
That's a remarkable response.

22:30.757 --> 22:33.342
And this translation, the CSV kind of ruins it for me.

22:33.803 --> 22:39.794
It says C. And the reason it says C is because we don't use the word that's in like the old King James, which is behold.

22:39.874 --> 22:43.838
She was like, behold, yes, okay, I'm in.

22:44.219 --> 22:47.542
She's not just saying, well, let's see, should we do this?

22:47.723 --> 22:50.706
She's like, no, I am completely and utterly in.

22:51.146 --> 22:52.328
I am the Lord's servant.

22:52.348 --> 22:57.293
What you have said, let it happen to me, no matter what that means for my life, I am in.

22:57.353 --> 23:08.786
And I think that's so astonishing because we are so oriented toward controlling our own destiny and making our own choices, that a statement like that rattles us.

23:09.250 --> 23:10.433
She didn't ask for this.

23:11.496 --> 23:13.501
It was going to cause her public disgrace.

23:14.383 --> 23:15.687
People would not believe her.

23:16.810 --> 23:21.843
We are so in our culture used to unwed pregnancies, but it would be shameful in her culture.

23:22.966 --> 23:24.530
The fact that she had a son

23:24.738 --> 23:30.285
before she had consummated this relationship would be the news to everyone in town.

23:30.345 --> 23:34.330
She was likely from a very poor family marrying a very poor man.

23:34.370 --> 23:35.892
They were just scraping by.

23:36.213 --> 23:44.884
And the fact that she was pregnant out of wedlock was gonna cause insults and possibly the loss of her fiance and the cruel treatment for her son and the cruel treatment for her.

23:45.224 --> 23:49.470
And she says, behold, may it happen to me exactly as you have said.

23:49.510 --> 23:52.594
That's rattling.

23:54.274 --> 23:59.459
Now it'd be easy right now at this juncture to make Mary out to be the hero.

24:00.780 --> 24:02.002
And she is pretty amazing.

24:02.202 --> 24:04.724
The more people have been named after Mary than any other woman in the world.

24:05.665 --> 24:08.027
But here's what's even more amazing to consider.

24:09.269 --> 24:15.074
Just like Abram, the 75 year old dude that 4,000 years ago was just picked out of nowhere.

24:16.255 --> 24:19.198
There was nothing actually that special about Mary.

24:20.700 --> 24:22.962
They each had an encounter

24:23.810 --> 24:36.903
with the most high God who bent heaven down to them and changed the trajectory of their lives in a way that nobody could have predicted would have happened.

24:37.043 --> 24:43.149
Abram, he wouldn't have picked war and famine and running out to save his nephew when he was an old codger, right?

24:43.749 --> 24:52.658
Mary wouldn't have picked ridicule or shame, but when the most high calls you, he changes your priority from the inside out.

24:54.370 --> 25:00.437
If you say, like, I follow Jesus, but my life hasn't changed, I have a few follow up questions.

25:01.719 --> 25:11.591
Because when you have engaged with the most high God, when you have come face to face with the son of the most high, everything in your world changes from the inside out.

25:11.631 --> 25:19.581
Listen to the words of the son of the most high just a few chapters later in Luke 6.

25:20.843 --> 25:23.666
He said, but I say to you, to anyone who'd listen,

25:24.034 --> 25:24.755
Love your enemies.

25:26.899 --> 25:28.482
This is what the son of the most high says to you.

25:29.444 --> 25:31.407
Do what is good to those who hate you.

25:32.710 --> 25:33.932
Bless those who curse you.

25:33.952 --> 25:36.516
Pray for those who mistreat you.

25:37.258 --> 25:39.882
If anyone hits you on the cheek, offer your other one also.

25:40.644 --> 25:43.449
And if anyone takes away your coat, don't hold back your shirt either.

25:44.370 --> 25:48.658
Give to everyone who asks you and from someone who takes your things, don't ask for them back.

25:49.570 --> 25:53.895
Just as you want for others to do for you, do the same for them.

25:53.935 --> 25:56.558
If you love those who love you, what credits that to you?

25:56.618 --> 25:59.140
Even sinners love those who love them.

26:00.041 --> 26:09.071
And if you lend to those who expect to receive what credit is that you, even sinners lend to sinners to be repaid in full, but love your enemies.

26:10.193 --> 26:11.074
Do what is good.

26:11.955 --> 26:16.099
Lend expecting nothing in return, and then your reward will be great.

26:16.660 --> 26:18.802
You will be children

26:19.074 --> 26:29.199
of the most high, for he is gracious to the ungrateful, and he is gracious to the evil.

26:30.061 --> 26:35.474
So be merciful, just as your Father, the God most high.

26:36.290 --> 26:38.012
is also merciful.

26:38.032 --> 26:44.639
You know the only reason we can even dream of doing any of these things that he has just called us to.

26:44.659 --> 26:56.132
The only reason we would want to do any of the things that he has just called us to is because this son of the most high, in the words of the Psalmist, stooped low to us.

26:56.212 --> 26:58.735
He sits high and he stoops low.

26:58.975 --> 27:01.618
And when we were his enemy, he loved us.

27:02.114 --> 27:10.422
When we mistreated him, he took it not just on the cheek, but he had nails pierced through his hand and he died on the cross for us.

27:10.482 --> 27:17.309
When we were evil, he was gracious and merciful when we were ungrateful to him.

27:17.369 --> 27:23.495
And when that truth pierces deep into your soul, it will change you.

27:24.856 --> 27:26.598
It'll make you more like him.

27:26.638 --> 27:30.482
And then it won't matter one bit

27:31.170 --> 27:33.673
Which one of us is the greatest?

27:34.975 --> 27:36.658
Because it'll be about Jesus, who is?

27:38.100 --> 27:38.500
Let's pray.

27:38.520 --> 27:43.948
Heavenly Father, we thank You for this remarkable story.

27:45.810 --> 27:50.317
And we thank You that Jesus is the Son of the Most High God.

27:50.357 --> 27:59.890
And we thank You that because of Jesus, we who have placed our faith in Him can also become the children, the sons and daughters

28:00.034 --> 28:01.216
of the Most High God.

28:01.716 --> 28:06.443
And so we just pray that you would transform us from the inside out.

28:07.465 --> 28:13.073
Make us more like your son, not for our glory, but for his glory.

28:14.555 --> 28:19.663
And we just pray that this Christmas season we would reflect who he is in our world.

28:20.564 --> 28:23.148
We pray this all in Jesus' precious name.

28:24.049 --> 28:24.530
Amen.

